# Google Ads API Configuration
# Get these credentials from Google Cloud Console + Google Ads

# Google Ads Developer Token (requires approval from Google)
# Apply here: https://developers.google.com/google-ads/api/docs/get-started/dev-token
GOOGLE_ADS_DEVELOPER_TOKEN=your-developer-token-here

# OAuth2 Credentials from Google Cloud Console
# Create OAuth 2.0 Client ID: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
GOOGLE_ADS_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
GOOGLE_ADS_CLIENT_SECRET=your-client-secret-here

# Instructions:
# 1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/
# 2. Create/select project
# 3. Enable "Google Ads API"
# 4. Create OAuth 2.0 Client ID (Web application)
#    - Authorized redirect URIs: http://localhost:8000/api/google-ads/oauth/callback
# 5. Apply for Developer Token in Google Ads account (Manager account recommended)
# 6. Wait 1-2 weeks for approval
# 7. Add these values to your main .env file
